description.plain:
Riley Davies, professionally known as ArrDee, (Born September 17 2002) is an artist hailing from Brighton, England and is quickly rising to be one of England’s most exciting emerging artists. His name derives from the pronunciation of his initials – RD.

Originally wowing fans through freestyles on social media sites such as Instagram, one of the first appearances from illusive Brighton artist came in the form of a BL@CKBOX Freestyle in 2019 which gained a steady attraction.

ArrDee gave his fans his first track on January 24th, 2021, releasing “Cheeky Bars.” The song provided ArrDee a platform to reach new heights, the music video garnering over 3 million views since its release. It wouldn’t be long until the he released his next project, as ArrDee would drop “6am In Brighton” in March 2021.

The Brighton native would drop a verse on Russ Millions & Tion Wayne’s “Body (Remix),” which went viral on TikTok. He would jump into the studio shortly after with Fumez The Engineer, releasing a highly anticipated freestyle for his Plugged In series, just 2 weeks later.

Capitalising off his newfound attention, ArrDee dropped his fourth single “Oliver Twist” in June 2021, which went viral on TikTok as expected. The song is his biggest hit to date, debuting at #7 on UK’s Official Charts.

songs.title: Oliver Twist

description.plain:
In “Oliver Twist,” ArrDee returns to his hometown of Brighton to showcase his trademark “cheeky” attitude and confidence in the wake of his recent success, marking the rapper’s third single.

The song arrives in response to his feature on Russ Millions & Tion Wayne’s April 2021 “Body (Remix)” — gaining traction on TikTok — and propelling ArrDee into the limelight; the song first previewed on ArrDee’s TikTok account in May 2021 and a tweet confirming a June 2021 release was posted shortly after.

In June 2021, the song attracted the attention of Ed Sheeran, who covered “Oliver Twist” whilst appearing on Capital XTRA:

https://youtu.be/28RXwM1O9OI?t=412

songs.title: Flowers (Say My Name)

description.plain:
“Flowers (Say My Name)” is the latest single from up-and-coming Brighton MC ArrDee and follows his July 2021 single “Jiggy (Whiz)”. The single was originally teased on TikTok on the 14th of October 2021. The official video of the single also features ArrDee’s rumoured girlfriend, Instagram model Angelyssia.

The single is inspired by Sweet Female Attitude’s iconic April 2000’s UK Garage classic “Flowers”, in which it samples, as well as Destiny’s Child’s iconic 1999 single “Say My Name”.

Juxtaposing the latter songs, ArrDee strays away from a conventional love song and navigates through topics such as the trust issues that come with a relationship and his bachelor lifestyle.

description.plain:
Assisted by UK vocalist Lola Young, ArrDee reflects on his come-up in the UK rap scene on “Who Woulda Thought,” progressing from his humble beginnings to having multiple Top 10 hits under his belt.

The beat is led by a piano pattern and quiet strings, which evolve into a more evocative section as the song progresses.
